    EFCTV_DTS,
    datediff(to_date(EFCTV_DTS), to_date(TRNSCTN_DT)) AS diff_days,
    months_between(to_date(EFCTV_DTS), to_date(TRNSCTN_DT)) AS diff_months,
    DELETION_STATUS,
    INTERNAL_ANALYSIS_VISIBILITY,
    VALIDATION_VISIBILITY,
    DWH_CREATE_DTS,
    DWH_UPDATE_DTS
FROM core.curated_idw_mtr_athn_mqs.dim_audit_rating_quote_permissions
WHERE DWH_CREATE_DTS >= timestamp('2026-04-14 05:00:00')
  AND LOWER(TRNSCTN_DESC) LIKE '%renewal%'
  AND (
        LATEST_QUOTE_JOURNEY_DESC IS NULL
        OR LATEST_QUOTE_JOURNEY_DESC NOT LIKE '%Sale%'
      )
  AND datediff(to_date(EFCTV_DTS), to_date(TRNSCTN_DT)) > 30
ORDER BY diff_days DESC
LIMIT 200;

Key thing to validate: for Renewal, EFCTV_DTS may naturally be far ahead of TRNSCTN_DT because renewal quotes can be generated well before policy renewal effective date. So the same 30-day rule may be valid for New Business, but not necessarily for Renewal.
